    "recap_headline": "Northwestern University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "EVANSTON, Ill. \u2013\nNorthwestern walked off No. 25 USC, 2-1 in the series finale to split Saturday's doubleheader at Miller Park.\u00a0The Trojans entered Saturday as the last remaining unbeaten team in Division I.\nLOGAN DE GROOT WALKS IT OFF! 'CATS WIN!\npic.twitter.com/V1Wjc6sWXy\n\u2014 Northwestern Baseball (@NUCatsBaseball)\nMarch 14, 2026\nGame One - USC 2, Northwestern 0\nNo. 25 USC secured a series victory with a 2-0 win in game one of Saturday's doubleheader.\nRHP\nGarrett Shearer\nwas solid in the start for Northwestern (6-9-1, 0-2 Big Ten), working 4.0 hitless innings, striking out four and allowing just two walks.\nUSC (19-0, 5-0 Big Ten) grabbed the lead in the top of the sixth, taking a 1-0 lead on an RBI single by OF Kevin Takeuchi. The Trojans added a run in the top of the eighth on a sacrifice bunt by OF Andrew Lamb to stretch their lead to 2-0.\nRHP Grant Govel (5-0) tossed 7.0 shutout innings for the Trojans, striking out six and allowing just two hits.\nRHP Adam Troy collected his sixth save of the season, entering with a runner on first and one out, retiring the final two batters of the game.\nGame Two - Northwestern 2, USC 1\nThe Wildcats handed USC its first loss of the season, walking off the Trojans, 2-1, in the bottom of the ninth.\nThree Wildcat pitchers combined to allow just one run on three hits in the contest, matching USC's season low.\nNorthwestern (7-9-1, 1-2 Big Ten) jumped out to an early lead, going ahead 1-0 in the bottom of the first. OF\nJack Lausch\nled off the inning with a double, and INF\nNick Barron\nbrought him home with a double of his own to give NU the lead.\nRHP\nMatt Kouser\ntossed 4.1 scoreless innings, allowing just one hit and striking out a pair in the start.\nUSC (19-1, 5-1 Big Ten) clawed back to knot the game at one apiece with a run in the eighth.\nIn the bottom of the ninth, INF\nNick Barron\nled off the inning with a base hit through the left side. After pinch runner\nJake Yang\nadvanced to second on a sacrifice bunt and moved over to third on a groundout, OF\nLogan de Groot\ndrove him in for the game-winning run to secure the victory.\nRHP\nSam Hliboki\n(2-2) earned the win for the Wildcats, allowing one run on two hits, striking out four in 4.1 innings pitched.\nNorthwestern continues Big Ten play when it begins a seven-game road swing with a three-game series at Oregon next weekend."
